ecn_liquid_penetration	Misc	true	Engine Combustion Network		Liquid Penetration Length							https://ecn.sandia.gov/diesel-spray-combustion/experimental-diagnostics/liquid-penetration-length/			Accessed 30 March 2026	https://ecn.sandia.gov/diesel-spray-combustion/experimental-diagnostics/liquid-penetration-length/	downloaded	reference_sources/ecn_liquid_penetration.html		thesis.tex:135 || thesis.tex:191 || thesis.tex:582 || thesis.tex:1513	thesis_zh.tex:135 || thesis_zh.tex:186 || thesis_zh.tex:272 || thesis_zh.tex:1330	Spray-imaging literature also reminds us that penetration, cone angle, and boundary position are not method-independent absolute truths; instead, they are operational observables produced jointly by the diagnostic method, thresholding rule, and post-processing definition, meaning repeatable quantities defined by an arbitrary measurement protocol rather than physical truths independent of that protocol \cite{MagnottiGenzale2013,JohnsonNaberLee2012,ecn_liquid_penetration,ecn_liquid_penetration_accessory}. || The extracted spray boundary is interpreted as a Mie-defined liquid-envelope observable under a specific optical protocol, not as full in-cylinder liquid truth \cite{ecn_liquid_penetration,ecn_liquid_penetration_accessory}. || By testing nominally identical injectors (Spray~A and Spray~D) across multiple institutions, ECN found measurable inter-facility variation in liquid-penetration values, and concluded explicitly that optically measured liquid boundaries should be understood as quantities defined by a particular measurement protocol, not as absolute ground-truth representations of the liquid phase \cite{ecn_liquid_penetration,ecn_liquid_penetration_accessory,MeijerECN2012}. || It does not directly quantify local liquid mass, droplet size, phase state, or wall-film potential \cite{ecn_liquid_penetration,ecn_liquid_penetration_accessory}.	ŚĖ∑ťõĺśąźŚÉŹśĖáÁĆģšĻüŤ°®śėéÔľĆÁ©Ņś∑Ī„ÄĀťĒ•ŤßíŚíĆŤĺĻÁēĆšĹćÁĹģŚĻ∂ťĚěŤĄĪÁ¶ĽśĖĻś≥ēŤÄĆŚ≠ėŚú®ÁöĄÁĽĚŚĮĻÁúüŚÄľÔľĆ ŤÄĆśėĮÁĒĪŤĮäśĖ≠śĖĻŚľŹ„ÄĀťėąŚÄľŤßĄŚąôŚíĆŚźéŚ§ĄÁźÜŚģöšĻČŚÖĪŚźĆÁĒüśąźÁöĄśďćšĹúśÄßŤßāśĶčťáŹÔľĆ Ść≥šĺĚŤĶĖŚÖ∑šĹďśĶčťáŹŚćŹŤģģŚģöšĻČÁöĄŚŹĮťáćŚ§ćťáŹÔľĆŤÄĆťĚěÁč¨ÁęčšļéśĖĻś≥ēÁöĄÁČ©ÁźÜÁúüŚÄľ \cite{MagnottiGenzale2013,JohnsonNaberLee2012,ecn_liquid_penetration,ecn_liquid_penetration_accessory}„Äā || śČÄśŹźŚŹĖÁöĄŚĖ∑ťõĺŤĺĻÁēĆŤĘęŤß£ťáäšłļÁČĻŚģöŚÖČŚ≠¶--ŚźéŚ§ĄÁźÜŚćŹŤģģšłčÁĒĪ Mie śąźŚÉŹŚģöšĻČÁöĄś∂≤ÁõłŚĆÖÁĽúŤßāśĶčťáŹÔľĆ ŤÄĆťĚěŚģĆśēīÁöĄÁľłŚÜÖś∂≤ÁõłÁúüŚÄľ \cite{ecn_liquid_penetration,ecn_liquid_penetration_accessory}„Äā || Engine Combustion NetworkÔľąECNÔľČÁöĄŚüļŚáÜÁ†ĒÁ©∂šłļŤŅôÁßćśĖĻś≥ēšĺĚŤĶĖśÄßśŹźšĺõšļÜÁ≥ĽÁĽüŤĮĀśćģÔľö ECN Śú®Ś§öšł™śúļśěĄśĶčŤĮēŚźćšĻČšłäÁõłŚźĆÁöĄŚĖ∑ś≤ĻŚô®ÔľąSpray~A ŚíĆ Spray~DÔľČÔľĆŚŹĎÁéįś∂≤ÁõłÁ©Ņś∑ĪŚú®šłćŚźĆŤģĺśĖĹŚíĆŚźéŚ§ĄÁźÜŚģöšĻČšĻčťóīŚ≠ėŚú®ŚŹĮŤßāśĶčŚ∑ģŚľāÔľĆŚĻ∂śėéÁ°ģŚįÜŚÖČŚ≠¶ś∂≤ÁõłŤĺĻÁēĆÁēĆŚģöšłļÁĒĪÁČĻŚģöśĶčťáŹŚćŹŤģģŚģöšĻČÁöĄťáŹÔľĆŤÄĆťĚěś∂≤ÁõłÁúüŚģěŚąÜŚłÉÁöĄÁĽĚŚĮĻŤ°®Á§ļ \cite{ecn_liquid_penetration,ecn_liquid_penetration_accessory,MeijerECN2012}„Äā || ŚģÉŚĻ∂šłćŤÉĹÁõīśé•ťáŹŚĆĖŚĪÄťÉ®ś∂≤šĹďŤī®ťáŹ„ÄĀś∂≤śĽīŚįļŚĮł„ÄĀÁõłśÄĀÔľĆśąĖŚ£ĀŤÜúŚĹĘśąźśĹúŚäõ \cite{ecn_liquid_penetration,ecn_liquid_penetration_accessory}„Äā	Supports the ECN definition and method-dependence of liquid-penetration measurements.	ÁĒ®šļéśĒĮśíĎ ECN ŚĮĻś∂≤ÁõłÁ©Ņś∑ĪŚģöšĻČŚŹäŚÖ∂śĖĻś≥ēšĺĚŤĶĖśÄßÁöĄŤĮīśėé„Äā	Saved public HTML page from https://ecn.sandia.gov/diesel-spray-combustion/experimental-diagnostics/liquid-penetration-length/
ecn_liquid_penetration_accessory	Misc	true	Engine Combustion Network		Accessory Data Regarding Liquid Penetration and Extinction at Spray A Conditions							https://ecn.sandia.gov/accessory-data-reguarding-liquid-penetration-and-extinction-at-spray-a-conditions/			Accessed 30 March 2026	https://ecn.sandia.gov/accessory-data-reguarding-liquid-penetration-and-extinction-at-spray-a-conditions/	downloaded	reference_sources/ecn_liquid_penetration_accessory.html		thesis.tex:135 || thesis.tex:191 || thesis.tex:582 || thesis.tex:1513	thesis_zh.tex:135 || thesis_zh.tex:186 || thesis_zh.tex:272 || thesis_zh.tex:1330	Spray-imaging literature also reminds us that penetration, cone angle, and boundary position are not method-independent absolute truths; instead, they are operational observables produced jointly by the diagnostic method, thresholding rule, and post-processing definition, meaning repeatable quantities defined by an arbitrary measurement protocol rather than physical truths independent of that protocol \cite{MagnottiGenzale2013,JohnsonNaberLee2012,ecn_liquid_penetration,ecn_liquid_penetration_accessory}. || The extracted spray boundary is interpreted as a Mie-defined liquid-envelope observable under a specific optical protocol, not as full in-cylinder liquid truth \cite{ecn_liquid_penetration,ecn_liquid_penetration_accessory}. || By testing nominally identical injectors (Spray~A and Spray~D) across multiple institutions, ECN found measurable inter-facility variation in liquid-penetration values, and concluded explicitly that optically measured liquid boundaries should be understood as quantities defined by a particular measurement protocol, not as absolute ground-truth representations of the liquid phase \cite{ecn_liquid_penetration,ecn_liquid_penetration_accessory,MeijerECN2012}. || It does not directly quantify local liquid mass, droplet size, phase state, or wall-film potential \cite{ecn_liquid_penetration,ecn_liquid_penetration_accessory}.	ŚĖ∑ťõĺśąźŚÉŹśĖáÁĆģšĻü