liu2020sprayreview	Article	true	Liu, Long and Peng, Yan and Liu, Dai and Han, Changfu and Zhao, Ningbo and Ma, Xiuzhen	2020	A Review of Phenomenological Spray Penetration Modeling for Diesel Engines with Advanced Injection Strategy	International Journal of Spray and Combustion Dynamics		12			10.1177/1756827720934067					https://doi.org/10.1177/1756827720934067	manual_required		No clearly legal open PDF/HTML download was found automatically; use the DOI/URL manually or through institutional access if needed.	thesis.tex:118 || thesis.tex:153 || thesis.tex:399 || thesis.tex:592	thesis_zh.tex:123 || thesis_zh.tex:151 || thesis_zh.tex:326	High-fidelity CFD is information-rich, but it requires complex inputs, model tuning, and substantial computational resources; existing reacting diesel-spray LES studies show that a single higher-fidelity simulation can consume tens of thousands of CPU core-hours \cite{CurtisNiemeyerSung2017,liu2020sprayreview}. || Recent studies have shown that neural networks can predict macroscopic spray properties such as penetration and cone angle from operating-condition parameters, forming a fast predictive layer between full CFD and empirical models \cite{VazKarathanasis2026,liu2020sprayreview}. || At high injection pressures, internal cavitation inside the nozzle can further alter the jet structure and atomisation characteristics in ways that classical penetration correlations make no attempt to capture \cite{liu2020sprayreview}. || Neural-network approaches have been used to map operating-condition parameters directly to spray tip penetration and cone angle without paying the cost of a full CFD computation in between, with several studies reporting close agreement against reference penetration data \cite{VazKarathanasis2026,liu2020sprayreview}.	ťęėšŅĚÁúü CFD šŅ°śĀĮšłįŚĮĆÔľĆšĹÜšĺĚŤĶĖŚ§ćśĚāŤĺďŚÖ•„ÄĀś®°ŚěčŤįÉŚŹāšłéśėĺŤĎóŤģ°ÁģóŤĶĄśļźÔľõ Ś∑≤śúČŚŹćŚļĒśüīś≤ĻŚĖ∑ťõĺ LES Á†ĒÁ©∂śėĺÁ§ļÔľĆŚćēś¨°ŤĺÉťęėšŅĚÁúüšĽŅÁúüŚć≥ŚŹĮś∂ąŤÄóśēįšłá CPU core-hours \cite{CurtisNiemeyerSung2017,liu2020sprayreview}„Äā || ŤŅĎśúüÁ†ĒÁ©∂Ť°®śėéÔľĆÁ•ěÁĽŹÁĹĎÁĽúŚŹĮšĽ•ŚüļšļéŚ∑•ŚÜĶŚŹāśēįťĘĄśĶčŚĖ∑ťõĺÁ©Ņś∑ĪŚíĆťĒ•ŤßíÁ≠ČŚģŹŤßāÁČĻśÄßÔľĆ šĽéŤÄĆŚú®ŚģĆśēī CFD šłéÁĽŹť™Ćś®°ŚěčšĻčťóīŚĹĘśąźŚŅęťÄüťĘĄśĶčŚĪā \cite{VazKarathanasis2026,liu2020sprayreview}„Äā || ŚÖĪŤĹ®ŚĖ∑ŚįĄÁ≥ĽÁĽüšł≠ÔľĆťíąťėÄŚľÄŚźĮŚíĆŚÖ≥ťó≠ťÉĹśėĮśúČťôźśó∂ťóīÁöĄśúļśĘįŤŅáÁ®čÔľõ Śú®ťíąťėÄŚģĆŚÖ®śä¨ŤĶ∑šĽ•ŚČćÔľĆśúČśēąśĶĀťÄöťĚĘÁßĮťöŹśó∂ťóīŚŹėŚĆĖÔľĆÁě¨śó∂ŚĖ∑ŚįĄÁéáŚíĆŤŅĎŚėīśĶĀŚúļšľöśĆĀÁĽ≠ŤĘęŤįÉŚą∂ÔľĆťęėŚéčšłčÁöĄŚĖ∑ŚėīŚÜÖśĶĀŚä®„ÄĀŚŹĮŤÉĹÁöĄÁ©ļŚĆĖšĽ•ŚŹäŚáļŚŹ£ťôĄŤŅĎÁöĄťõĺŚĆĖÁä∂śÄĀŚŹąšľöŤŅõšłÄś≠•śĒĻŚŹėŚįĄśĶĀÁĽďśěĄ \cite{StumppRicco1996,HiroyasuArai1990,liu2020sprayreview}„Äā	Supports the review of phenomenological spray-penetration models and their limitations for advanced injection strategies.	ÁĒ®šļéśĒĮśíĎÁéįŤĪ°Ś≠¶Á©Ņś∑Īś®°ŚěčÁĽľŤŅįŚŹäŚÖ∂Śú®ŚÖąŤŅõŚĖ∑ŚįĄÁ≠ĖÁē•šłčÁöĄŚĪÄťôź„Äā	Checked direct URL, arXiv when applicable, and OpenAlex OA metadata.
peraza2022swi	Article	true	Peraza, Jose E. and Payri, Raul and Gimeno, Jaime and Carvallo, Cesar	2022	Analysis of Spray/Wall Impingement Using an ECN Single-Hole Injector and a Controlled-Temperature Wall Under Realistic Engine Conditions	Applied Thermal Engineering		208		118167	10.1016/j.applthermaleng.2022.118167					https://doi.org/10.1016/j.applthermaleng.2022.118167	manual_required		No clearly legal open PDF/HTML download was found automatically; use the DOI/URL manually or through institutional access if needed.	thesis.tex:95 || thesis.tex:668 || thesis.tex:694 || thesis.tex:1517	thesis_zh.tex:105 || thesis_zh.tex:473 || thesis_zh.tex:505 || thesis_zh.tex:1332	If its liquid envelope reaches the piston bowl or cylinder wall before a useful ignition kernel forms, wall wetting, lubricant dilution, degraded local mixture preparation, and increased unburned-hydrocarbon emissions may follow \cite{peraza2022swi,ahmad2025fueldilution,MorieiraMotaPanao2010}. || When liquid fuel reaches the piston bowl or cylinder wall before evaporation or ignition has had time to consume it, a fuel film deposits on the surface, and the downstream consequences --- wall wetting, locally deteriorated mixing, elevated unburned-hydrocarbon emissions, and lubricant dilution --- are well documented across both passenger-car and heavy-duty contexts \cite{peraza2022swi,ahmad2025fueldilution,MorieiraMotaPanao2010}. || }\ measured spray impingement on a controlled-temperature flat wall using a single-hole injector and characterized how the penetration-to-wall-distance relationship deforms with ambient density and temperature \cite{peraza2022swi}. || The regime of primary concern is direct liquid-wall contact and persistent wall-film formation \cite{MorieiraMotaPanao2010,liu2024marine_impingement,peraza2022swi,ahmad2025fueldilution}.	Ťč•ś∂≤ÁõłŚĆÖÁĽúŚú®ŚĹĘśąźśúČśēąÁāĻÁĀęś†łšĻčŚČćŚ∑≤Ťß¶ŚŹäśīĽŚ°ěť°∂śąĖÁľłŚ£ĀÔľĆ ŚąôŚŹĮŤÉĹŚĮľŤáīŚ£ĀťĚĘś∂¶śĻŅ„ÄĀś∂¶śĽĎś≤ĻÁ®Äťáä„ÄĀŚĪÄťÉ®ś∑∑ŚźąśĀ∂ŚĆĖšĽ•ŚŹäśú™ÁáÉÁĘ≥śįĘśéíśĒ